    <h1>JOVIAN LIM, 36, PHO&#xAD;TOG&#xAD;RA&#xAD;PHER</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201218/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-18"><time>2020-12-18</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Aman&#xAD;dac@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>“I work i n an imag­ing com­pany called Of­fice. Lately, I have been try­ing to fin­ish up photograph­y projects that were de­layed or post­poned be­cause of the cir­cuit breaker. My last shoot was space photograph­y for the re­designed wom­enswear stu­dio</p>
    <p>Time Taken To</p>
    <p>Make A Dress.</p>
    <p>I work from home or my stu­dio in Kaki Bukit, but as home spa­ces are be­com­ing work spa­ces as well, I have a re­newed in­ter­est in mak­ing my liv­ing space as com­fort­able as pos­si­ble. I would love this No­mad rug (from US$445 or S$590, above) from Nordic Knots. It is made in small batches and spe­cial be­cause it is de­signed in col­lab­o­ra­tion with a tat­too artist.</p>
    <p>If the sky’s the limit, I have this Veer Cruiser stroller wagon (US$599, top) on my wish list. As a new par­ent, I want to safely take my six-month-old daugh­ter out­doors, and this is func­tional and sleek yet rugged enough for an out­door ad­ven­ture with her.</p>
    <p>I’m look­ing for­ward to spend­ing Christ­mas with my im­me­di­ate fam­ily – the Lims and the Lams – and tak­ing the last week of the year to pause and re­flect on what a wild year it has been. De­spite all the dis­rup­tion to the econ­omy, there is still plenty to be grate­ful for.”</p>

